Get a fully functional static version of your WordPress website. 

== Description ==

Produces a static snapshot of your WordPress site.
Files are renamed with the correct extension if they come from a CDN.
All links produced are relative - they won't redirect to the original website but to the other static files.

This plugin is a wrapper for the Linux/Unix wget application. Your server must use Linux/Unix!

This is a BETA version of the product. Please DO NOT USE IT on a production site. 


== Installation ==

1. Download the plugin
1. Activate the plugin through the 'Plugins' menu in WordPress
1. A new item "Get Snapshot" is now available from the WordPress admin sidebar

== Frequently Asked Questions ==

= Will this plugin work locally on a Windows machine? =

No. This plugin can only work locally with Linux or Unix. 
Max OSX users need to be sure that wget is installed on their machine
http://osxdaily.com/2012/05/22/install-wget-mac-os-x/

